</picture></div><p>The 10-step blueprint to opening your own bar.</p></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section1" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>1.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=decide-what-type-of-bar-you-would-like-to-open>Decide what type of bar you would like to open.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section1-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=look-into-the-different-types-of-bars-you-can-open>Look into the different types of bars you can open.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-look-into-the-different-types-of-bars-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Look into the different types of bars you can open."></div></div><p>The type of bar you choose informs everything about your bar, including its design, location, dimensions, choice of alcohol and food, and its personality. There are five distinct categories of bars: sports bars, neighborhood bars, beer bars or tap houses, brewpubs or breweries, and specialty bars.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>Sports bars</strong> cater to a very specific clientele, often with very specific needs. People come to sports bars to watch sports and drink beer, in that order. However, sports bars are also expected to serve a variety of foods and snacks. Sports bar menus typically include burgers, pizza, barbecue wings, nachos, etc.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Creating an optimal viewing experience is your primary goal in a sports bar, so you will need to invest in television screens of varying sizes, as well as audio and lighting equipment. You will also need to make certain that each seat has a good view of a television before you think about alcohol.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>Neighborhood bars</strong> are ubiquitous across America, but their revenues vary and are dependent on location and market. One constant with neighborhood bars is a loyal consumer base. These bars don't demand much in terms of style and variety. What they need to do is create a space that a community of people can share and call a "home away from home."</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Expect to invest in things that foster a sense of comfort, like pool tables, music machines, video games, or dartboards.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>Beer bars</strong> are cheaper to set up than other bars since a beer-only alcohol license typically costs far less and you will only be offering an assortment of beers (and possibly food) on your menu. Although location and market will influence your costs, less startup capital is required to set up a beer bar, with costs estimated at $20,000 to $100,000.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>Brewpubs</strong> are more expensive to set up because you are manufacturing your own beer and investing in your own brewing equipment and expertise, which will rocket your startup costs to an estimated $100,000 to $1 million.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>The upside of starting a brewpub is that you will own your very own, unique product that no other bar sells. Beyond quality, you also get to control the quantity of your product, giving you greater logistical power in your business operations.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>Specialty bars</strong> focus on one particular drink or theme, be they a wine-only bar or something more extravagant, like a cigar bar. Specialty bars are generally small, will have more personality than a regular bar, and will be located in upmarket neighborhoods. The location and type of alcohol sold will influence the startup costs of these establishments.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>One of the benefits of specialty bars is that they are very popular for parties, meetings, and corporate events. The last few years have seen a trend in the hiring of specialty bars to host such occasions.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section1-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=pick-a-name-for-your-bar>Pick a name for your bar.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-choose-a-name-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Pick a name for your bar."></div></div><p>Don't underestimate the value of a good name. Your bar name should be consistent with your bar type and brand and should resonate with your target audience. Remember that your bar name will be at the vanguard of your marketing efforts, so choose well.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Take a look at this article on <a
href="https://www.namesnack.com/guides/how-to-name-a-sports-bar">how to name a sports bar</a> for some great tips on naming your bar.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section2" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>2.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=create-a-bar-business-plan>Create a bar business plan.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section2-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=include-all-the-essential-elements-in-your-business-plan>Include all the essential elements in your business plan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-bar-business-plan-288x288-20200928.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Include all the essential elements in your business plan."></div></div><p>An effective business plan will achieve seven things:</p><ul><li>Summarize your business proposition.</li><li>Define your company structure.</li><li>Offer an extensive market analysis.</li><li>Detail your business offerings.</li><li>Describe your management plan and ownership structure.</li><li>Explain your marketing and advertising strategy.</li><li>Outline your financial projections.</li></ul><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>We've created a business plan template to help you get started. You'll find it toward the bottom of this page.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section2-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=know-who-your-customers-are>Know who your customers are.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-know-who-your-customers-are-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Know who your customers are."></div></div><p>As a prospective bar owner, you are presented with a choice: find a location and adapt to the local market, or find a market that your bar concept is suited to and establish your presence there.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>If you choose to find a location and adapt, you will need to gather market information about the area you are opening in before you decide on a bar concept. Data on demographics such as age, gender, and income levels will paint a picture of the type of customers you are likely to find.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>If you choose to find the right market for your concept, you will need to obtain statewide demographic data that would determine where your ideal area would be.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>In both cases, we recommend hiring a specialized marketing firm to research the local market, make sense of the data for you, and advise you on the proper course of action.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section2-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=study-your-competitors>Study your competitors.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-do-some-research-on-your-competitors-288x288-20200622-2.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Study your competitors."></div></div><p>Understanding your competitors involves gathering data on local bars for analysis. Again, we recommend hiring a marketing firm to accomplish this, but you could also carry out your own investigation.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Try visiting bars in the area and speaking to people. How busy are the bars? Are they as busy on weeknights as they are on weekends? What do they charge? How is their food? What kind of customers frequent the place? What do they think of the bar?</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Combine your quantitative and qualitative data to paint a detailed profile of your competition.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section3" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>3.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=form-your-bar-company>Form your bar company.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section3-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=set-up-a-legal-entity>Set up a legal entity.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-start-a-publishing-company-llc-288x288-20200812.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Set up a legal entity."></div></div><p>For a bar, you'll want to form a Limited Liability Company (LLC). LLC taxes are reasonable and they protect personal assets in the event that you default on a loan or are sued.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>You may also choose to set up a corporation, sole proprietorship, or partnership.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>To help you with the legal process, consider hiring a lawyer or business consultant.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section3-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=invest-in-business-insurance>Invest in business insurance.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-obtain-business-insurance-288x288-20200812.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Invest in business insurance."></div></div><p>There are two types of liability insurance every bar owner should get. Premise liability protects the business should someone get injured on your premises. Dram shop liability protects you in the event that you over-serve alcohol to a customer and a third party is involved in a road accident.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section3-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=obtain-the-necessary-licenses-and-permits>Obtain the necessary licenses and permits.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-license-and-permits-288x288-20200729.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Obtain the necessary licenses and permits."></div></div><p>Make sure you know about and have all the licenses and permits that you will need.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Find out more about obtaining a business license on the <a
href="https://www.sba.gov/business-guide/launch-your-business/apply-licenses-permits">Small Business Administration's (SBA) website</a>.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Liquor license rules differ from state to state, but <a
href="https://ballotpedia.org/Liquor_license_costs_by_state,_2018">this handy guide</a> will give you more information on each state's liquor license rules. Liquor license application forms can be obtained from your local Department of Alcoholic Beverage Control. The investigation process will typically take 45 to 60 days, with successful applicants waiting a further 30 days for issuing.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Registering with the IRS is critically important to avoid tax penalties. Be sure to <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-apply-for-an-ein">apply for an EIN</a>.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>A license for serving food will be required, ensuring that your bar adheres to safety and sanitation standards. Food licenses differ from state to state, but the license typically starts at $50.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>It's very important that you both protect your intellectual property and not infringe upon others. We recommend consulting with a trademark attorney to oversee the process.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Before undertaking any construction to renovate your space, you will need to submit your intentions to the local government.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>You will need to maintain a record book where you can track the names of your suppliers, the quantity of alcohol you purchase, and the dates of purchase. Failure to present a record book upon inspection could result in a fine of up to $10,000. In some cases, penalties could include imprisonment. Refer to <a
href="https://www.ttb.gov/ttb-audiences/business-owners/retailers-beverage-alcohol">the Alcohol and Tabacco Tax and Trade Bureau's guide</a> for further information.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section4" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>4.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=invest-in-the-right-technology>Invest in the right technology.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section4-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=purchase-a-reliable-point-of-sale-system>Purchase a reliable point of sale system.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-purchase-a-point-of-sales-system-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Purchase a reliable point of sale system."></div></div><p>POS systems process orders and sales and should have menu items and prices programmed into them to facilitate speedy transactions. The average price for a restaurant POS system is $50.00 to $80.00 per month, but there are plenty of free options too.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section4-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=invest-in-a-good-mobile-credit-card-reader>Invest in a good mobile credit card reader.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-invest-in-a-good-mobile-credit-card-reader-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Invest in a good mobile credit card reader."></div></div><p>Mobile credit card readers facilitate debit or credit card payments through smartphones or tablets.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section4-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=set-up-inventory-management-software>Set up inventory management software.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-buy-software-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Set up inventory management software."></div></div><p>Inventory management software aids in the management and tracking of materials, orders, and deliveries for your bar. If you want to avoid overstocking or under-stocking your liquor, investing in an inventory management tool is essential.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section4-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=get-a-good-payroll-software>Get a good payroll software.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-get-payroll-software-288x288-20200821.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Get a good payroll software."></div></div><p>Payroll software simplifies the employee payment process.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section5" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>5.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=source-funding-for-your-bar>Source funding for your bar.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section5-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=get-the-necessary-startup-capital-to-open-your-bar>Get the necessary startup capital to open your bar.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-franchise-loans-288x288-20200723.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Get the necessary startup capital to open your bar."></div></div><p>There are plenty of funding options available for aspiring bar owners, including SBA loans, banking loans, credit card financing, etc. You will need to be aware of maximum loan amounts, credit ratings, collateral, and interest rates.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Typical startup costs for a bar include a security deposit, equipment, and preparations at about $110,000; a liquor license and other permits at around $5,000; and inventory at around $6,000. This adds up to a total initial startup investment of approximately $121,000.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section5-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=look-into-operational-financing>Look into operational financing.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/decide-which-types-of-financing-you-need-288x288-20200814.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Look into operational financing."></div></div><p>There are two types of operational financing that you can use to open your bar and get started on making a profit.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>Invoice financing</strong> is a process whereby unpaid invoices can be leveraged to secure business credit. Instead of waiting for the invoices to be paid, businesses can use their unpaid invoices to obtain funding.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>Working capital loans</strong> are cash injections designed to help businesses experiencing short-term cash flow problems. These types of loans support a business's operational expenses during difficult periods.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Monthly expenses for a bar can get up to $26,000, with staff salaries totaling about $13,000, rent and utilities coming up to around $7,000, and inventory replenishment costing about $6,000 a month.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section6" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>6.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=choose-the-right-location>Choose the right location.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section6-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=evaluate-the-cost>Evaluate the cost.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-add-total-costs-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Evaluate the cost."></div></div><p>Ultimately, your budget will have the most say over the location of your bar. Determine how much you are able to spend on monthly rent and choose a location that offers potential.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section6-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=think-about-your-ideal-customer-demographics>Think about your ideal customer demographics.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-think-about-your-customer-demographics-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Think about your ideal customer demographics."></div></div><p>Once you know your brand and the type of customer you are selling to, it follows that you would choose a location frequented by your target market.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section6-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=research-your-competition>Research your competition.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-research-your-competitors-288x288-20200811_2020-08-11-134856_rbwp.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Research your competition."></div></div><p>Find out how many bars operate in your area. Too much competition can benefit the customer with competitive pricing, but competition can also be a good thing. A neighborhood with a strong service economy or presence of bars creates a pedestrian culture. You can also take advantage of your competitors bringing customers into the neighborhood.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section6-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=plan-for-optimum-visibility-for-your-bar>Plan for optimum visibility for your bar.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-consider-the-visibility-of-your-bar-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Plan for optimum visibility for your bar."></div></div><p>Some bars struggle with inactivity because their bar is not ideally located, while others prosper in the most unwelcoming areas because they offer a great experience.</p><p>While your location and level of service can greatly impact your bar, the general rule is to offer both. Bear in mind that visibility is positively correlated with rent, so areas that are easily accessible with a steady flow of pedestrians are likely to cost more.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section6-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=look-into-the-foot-traffic-of-the-location>Look into the foot traffic of the location.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-look-into-foot-traffic-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Look into the foot traffic of the location."></div></div><p>Opening your bar in an area with a strong pedestrian culture can do wonders for your business. An area frequented by people on foot will make a chance visit to your bar more likely.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section6-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=plan-for-parking-availability>Plan for parking availability.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-think-about-accessibility-and-parking-288x288-20200725.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Plan for parking availability."></div></div><p>Uber might have made getting around an easier task, but for patrons who prefer their own transport, parking is essential. If they have to walk far from a parking spot to your bar, they might just consider someplace else.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section6-step7" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.7&nbsp;</span><h4 id=research-neighborhood-crime-statistics>Research neighborhood crime statistics.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-research-neighborhood-crime-statistics-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Research neighborhood crime statistics."></div></div><p>If your neighborhood has a reputation for criminal activity, it may deter customers from coming to your bar. Check local crime statistics before setting up shop.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section7" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>7.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=find-the-right-supplier>Find the right supplier.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section7-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=ask-the-right-questions-when-researching-potential-suppliers>Ask the right questions when researching potential suppliers.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-research-potential-suppliers-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Ask the right questions when researching potential suppliers."></div></div><p>When looking for the right supplier, there are some important questions you need to ask. You need to know what brands they sell, whether they have specials or discounts, a minimum or maximum purchasing threshold, how often they make deliveries, and how much notice they need.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section7-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=find-a-supplier-in-your-area>Find a supplier in your area.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/how-to-name-a-restaurant-2.1-288x288-20200623.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Find a supplier in your area."></div></div><p>Check out the <a
href="https://beveragetradenetwork.com/en/liquor-distributors-in-usa-341.htm">Beverage Trade Network</a> for information on where to find suppliers in your area.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>It can be very helpful to have a supplier who can give you extra insights into the market, like which brands are trending right now.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section7-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=keep-in-mind-the-type-of-bar-you-are-opening>Keep in mind the type of bar you are opening.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-keep-in-mind-the-type-of-bar-you-are-opening-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Keep in mind the type of bar you are opening."></div></div><p>The type of bar you plan to open will influence the kind of supplier you need. If you're a specialty bar, you'll want to decide which brands of that particular alcohol you want to stock. If you serve a variety of drinks, you'll have to pair up with a supplier with a wide selection of choices.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section7-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=find-a-supplier-who-offers-a-range-of-alcohol-qualities>Find a supplier who offers a range of alcohol qualities.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-find-a-supplier-with-a-range-of-quality-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Find a supplier who offers a range of alcohol qualities."></div></div><p>Each type of alcohol typically comes in five categories of quality: well, call, premium, super premium, and top shelf, each with corresponding price categories. While it is not necessary to have all five categories, you should offer a broad range of choices. This gives customers different pricing options.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>You will need to manage your own inventory to determine what you need from your supplier. Managing your inventory involves using your existing sales data to determine how much alcohol you sell per night, then forecasting what you would need to order in the coming days or weeks.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Your first week without any sales data will serve as an experimental stage and it might be that you over or under-stock during this week, but that should provide you with the necessary data to make more accurate forecasting in the future.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section8" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>8.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=set-up-your-bar>Set up your bar.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section8-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=plan-the-layout-of-your-bar>Plan the layout of your bar.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-plan-the-layout-of-your-bar-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Plan the layout of your bar."></div></div><p>You will want to ensure that there will be a good flow around your bar counter as well as space for tables and movement between tables. Also, think about whether you want to add bar games (pool, darts, etc.), a dance floor and/or a stage for live music and deejays, and where your bathrooms will be located.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section8-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=create-a-list-of-the-essential-equipment-for-your-bar>Create a list of the essential equipment for your bar.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-essential-bar-equipment-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Create a list of the essential equipment for your bar."></div></div><p>The aim here is to find the right balance of quality and affordability. When purchasing these items, keep in mind that some of them will take up plenty of space, come with maintenance costs and safety risks, require cleaning and repairs, and will need to remain consistent with your design aesthetic. It is important that you plan and budget well.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section9" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>9.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=hire-the-right-staff>Hire the right staff.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section9-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>9.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=create-a-list-of-the-staff-you-need-for-your-bar>Create a list of the staff you need for your bar.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-create-a-list-of-the-staff-you-need-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Create a list of the staff you need for your bar."></div></div><p>In the beginning, you may decide to keep the number of staff limited while you build your client base and your profit margin. You may also find that you won't need certain positions, depending on the type of bar you want to open.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Some common bar staff includes a bartender, barista, bar manager, barback, cocktail waitresses and waiters, brewmaster, servers, kitchen manager, chef or cook, and food runners.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section9-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>9.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=advertise-your-job-openings>Advertise your job openings.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-use-software-to-advertise-and-hire-288x288-20200718.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Advertise your job openings."></div></div><p>You can use a job posting site to advertise positions and find the talent you need.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Finding the right staff is more than filling a skills gap. You need to ensure that all employees present themselves well and are in keeping with the image and atmosphere your bar wants to project.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section10" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>10.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=promote-your-bar>Promote your bar.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section10-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=host-an-opening-night>Host an opening night.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-have-a-grand-opening-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Host an opening night."></div></div><p>Your opening night should accomplish two things: it should run seamlessly, and it should make an impression on its attendees.</p><p>Many bars host both a soft and grand opening, as a soft opening can serve as a test run for your bar and give you an opportunity to iron out any flaws in your operations. You will also be able to get some feedback before you officially open your doors.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Hold a soft opening first with a "demo menu" of limited eating options to ease the stress on your staff. You could open for a short time, invite neighboring homes and businesses to get to know your local area and competition, or host a "friends and family" evening where you're with people you feel comfortable with to get honest feedback.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Hold a grand opening night and consider inviting some top social media influencers.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section10-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=hold-daily-specials>Hold daily specials.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-opening-specials-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Hold daily specials."></div></div><p>When you've been open for a while, you'll have a better understanding of which nights are your popular nights and which nights are in need of a boost. Target these low turnout periods with promotions and discounts to draw in more people.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Get creative with your promotions. You could make every day of the week a themed drink special. For example, Mondays could be 15% off all wines. This gives your customers a reason to buy a particular drink on any given night.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Have drink and food combination specials, where you pair a drink with a suitable eating option.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Set half-price specials with a time limit to draw in crowds at times of the day with a low customer turnout, or start a happy hour.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>When running these events, be sure to plan well for them. A good goal to aim for is a profit that's at least three times what the promotion costs you. Schedule your promotion a few weeks in advance, and don't set an end date in the event that you start losing money or want to keep it running longer.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section10-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=use-social-media>Use social media.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-use-social-media-288x288-2020071_2023-09-14-232756_xnib.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Use social media."></div></div><p>Social media marketing demands a level of creativity and research on the part of the marketer in order to achieve results. No one platform or strategy will guarantee success, as you will need to know more about who your audience is online and how they use social media.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Create Facebook, Instagram, and Twitter pages with a design aesthetic that matches that of your bar. Be sure to include high-quality pictures on your page. Use these platforms to advertise specials, run promotions, and get customer reviews and feedback for your bar.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Invite social media influencers to your bar to build a buzz online and offer them free drinks. Additionally, run a social media promotion by asking people to follow your account and tag your bar when they take a picture. Offer them a special discount on any drink as an incentive.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Create your very own hashtag and encourage customers to use the hashtag when posting. This is a great way for potential customers to find out what your bar is about and the type of people who go there.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>One way of better managing your marketing efforts is to invest in a marketing tool for your bar. These apps can be used to create campaigns, gather customer information, and manage all your communication channels.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-open-a-bar-section10-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=remember-to-use-search-engine-marketing>Remember to use search engine marketing.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-register-with-google-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Remember to use search engine marketing."></div></div><p>When customers in your area search Google for a sports bar, they are likely to use search terms such as "Sports bar near me." You'll want your bar to be at or near the top of the search results, making yourself attractive to potential customers.</p><p>Search engine marketing (SEM) helps you rank in Google search results, making you visible to more potential customers.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
